Brazilian Stock Movers: Fibria Declines; Petrobras, OGX Gain

-- B y   A l e x a n d e r   C u a d r o s
-- 
2011-10-11T20:27:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-11/brazilian-stock-movers-fibria-petrobras-decline-ogx-gains.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Sao Paulo  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close of trading. Preferred
shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa Index rose 1.1 percent to 53,838.47.  Fibria Celulose SA (FIBR3)  (FIBR3 BS) dropped 0.9 percent to 14.66
reais. The world’s largest pulp producer was cut to “neutral”
from “outperform” at Credit Suisse Group AG.  OGX Petroleo & Gas Participacoes SA (OGXP3 BS) advanced 3.1
percent to 12.29 reais.  Eike Batista , the oil company’s
billionaire controller, boosted his stake to 62.5 percent from
61 percent, according to the company’s press office.  Petroleo Brasileiro SA (PETR4)  (PETR4 BS) advanced 1.3 percent to
19.16 reais.  Brazil ’s state-controlled oil company followed
crude prices after they pared losses in  New York .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alexander Cuadros in Sao Paulo at 
 acuadros@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  